**`InjectOsloPolicyConfig` always injects even when path is empty**

The PR description and task spec both state: *"if policyFilePath is non-empty, ensure `oslo_policy` section exists and set `policy_file` key; if empty, no-op."* However, the current implementation unconditionally creates the `oslo_policy` section and writes `policy_file = ""` even when `policyFilePath` is an empty string. This will produce invalid configuration when no policy override is needed.

```suggestion
func InjectOsloPolicyConfig(config map[string]map[string]string, policyFilePath string) {
	if policyFilePath == "" {
		return
	}
	if config["oslo_policy"] == nil {
		config["oslo_policy"] = make(map[string]string)
	}
	config["oslo_policy"]["policy_file"] = policyFilePath
}
```
